title: Narrator_ColdOpen_MarinLetter
tags: narrator coldopen marin phase48
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Marin's letter — read by the Narrator in the Cold Open Cinematic.
// Author: Inara Vellis (Lead Memory Writer)
// Spec:   Docs/Phase48_DepthLayer_Signoff.md § 2 (Phase 48 — Cold Open)
//         Docs/Depth_Bible/03_WORLDBUILDING_AND_LORE.md § Predecessor
//         Codex 11 § Memory Dream Director (the letter doubles as a Dream
//           hook for post-M2 expansion — "the wedding ring on the windowsill")
//
// Voice signature (Vellis Rules § 4 — the Predecessor):
//   • Speaks AS IF to the player directly — "Whoever you are".
//   • Short sentences (~12 words avg) interrupted by em-dashes.
//   • References the candle by name; references the locked drawer by name.
//   • Mentions Pickle without naming her gender (she is "the cat").
//   • Never tells the player WHY she left — only that she did.
//   • Three-beat structure: (1) apology / disclaimer, (2) practical
//     bequest of objects, (3) one piece of inviolable instruction.
//
// Voice lineIds (D-058 / D-059 — canonical .wav file-swap paths):
//   narrator_marin_letter_01 — letter body line 1 (apology)
//   narrator_marin_letter_02 — letter body line 2 (instructions + bequest)
//
// Total word count: 72 words. Reads ~36 s at the human auditory comfort
// rate of 120 WPM. Lines up with the ColdOpenCinematicUI typewriter
// stage (~7 s default duration with adaptive cps locking).
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

<<scene "BlackVignette">>
<<eyes_look_at "candle">>

Narrator: Whoever you are —
<<wait 0.6>>
Narrator: if you are reading this, the candle in the Hollow lit again.
Narrator: I did not blow it out.

<<adjust_predecessor_warmth 4>>

Narrator: I went after the Forgotten Year, and I will not be back
Narrator: before you have settled. Polish the orbs slowly.
Narrator: Trust the bread before you trust the men.
<<wait 0.8>>
Narrator: And do not — do not — open the locked drawer until the cat tells you to.

<<eyes_look_at "signature">>
Narrator: — Marin, Keeper of the Hollow before you.

<<set $seen_cold_open = true>>
<<set $marin_letter_read = true>>
<<adjust_predecessor_warmth 8>>

===

title: Echo_Marin_Welcome
tags: echo marin hologram phase49
---
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Marin's Echo Hologram welcome — the first predecessor encounter in the
// Hollow. Plays on the player's first Activate() of the Echo interactable
// on the workbench, next to the parchment Note.
//
// Author: Inara Vellis (Lead Memory Writer) + Sven Aleko (Cutscenes)
// Spec:   Docs/Phase48_DepthLayer_Signoff.md § 2 (Phase 49 — Echo Hologram)
//         Docs/Depth_Bible/12_COMPANIONS_AND_FAMILIARS.md § Echo Hologram
//         Codex 03 § Predecessor
//
// Voice signature (continuation of the Narrator_ColdOpen voice):
//   • Slightly warmer than the letter — she's speaking to you face-to-face
//     now, not in writing. The pace is more conversational.
//   • Still no proper names exchanged. She does not know YOUR name; you
//     do not yet know HER full story.
//   • Three-beat structure matched to the cinematic visual: apology +
//     practical bequest (the workbench, the cat, the baker next door) +
//     one piece of inviolable instruction (trust the bread).
//   • Total ~17 s at 120 WPM. Lines up with the 3-line monologue spec
//     in EchoHologramInteractable.cs.
//
// Voice lineIds (D-058 / D-059 — canonical .wav file-swap paths):
//   echo_marin_welcome_01 — opening apology
//   echo_marin_welcome_02 — the bequest (candle, cat, baker)
//   echo_marin_welcome_03 — the inviolable instruction (trust the bread + Pickle's veto)
//
// Repeat-hearing fallback (when echoHologramHeard == true):
//   echo_marin_hum_01 — silent hum text
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

<<eyes_look_at "hologram_marin">>
<<play_animation "Marin" "fade_in_pale_blue">>
<<play_sfx "echo_marin_chord">>

<<if $echo_hologram_heard == false>>

    Marin: If the Hollow lit again, I am very sorry.
    Marin: You inherit it the way I did — without ceremony, without a manual.

    <<wait 0.6>>

    Marin: There is a candle on the workbench.
    Marin: There is a cat at your knee.
    Marin: There is a baker next door who has been waiting.

    <<wait 0.6>>

    Marin: Trust the bread.
    Marin: Polish slowly.
    Marin: And if Pickle sniffs a memory and walks away — you should walk away too.

    <<adjust_predecessor_warmth 12>>
    <<set $echo_hologram_heard = true>>
    <<set $echo_holograms_found = $echo_holograms_found + 1>>

<<else>>

    // Hum-only repeat — Marin's voice "doesn't return easily" per D-061.
    Marin: (The hologram hums but does not speak.)
    Marin: (Marin's voice doesn't return easily. You heard her once. Be patient.)

<<endif>>

<<play_animation "Marin" "fade_out">>

===

title: Narrator_Preface_Gentle
tags: narrator preface gentle phase50
---
// The Gentle-Mode preface beat. 3 lines, ~5 s total at 120 WPM.
// PrefaceBeatUI.cs gentleLines field default.

Narrator: There is a candle in the window.
<<wait 1.4>>
Narrator: There is no hurry.
<<wait 1.4>>
Narrator: Walk slowly. Doris is waiting.

<<set $preface_beat_played = true>>
<<set $preface_tone_bucket = "Gentle">>

===

title: Narrator_Preface_Standard
tags: narrator preface standard phase50
---
// The Standard preface beat (default). 3 lines, ~5 s total.

Narrator: The lane is quiet.
<<wait 1.4>>
Narrator: A candle waits in the window of the Hollow.
<<wait 1.4>>
Narrator: Doris is on her step. Walk.

<<set $preface_beat_played = true>>
<<set $preface_tone_bucket = "Standard">>

===

title: Narrator_Preface_Deep
tags: narrator preface deep phase50
---
// The Deep-tone preface beat. 3 lines, ~5 s total.

Narrator: You inherit what you do not choose.
<<wait 1.4>>
Narrator: The candle is waiting in the Hollow.
<<wait 1.4>>
Narrator: She is on her step. The lane is shorter than you think.

<<set $preface_beat_played = true>>
<<set $preface_tone_bucket = "Deep">>

===
